        public TransferKinInfoVector fUpdateFromTerms()

      • fRemove

        public TransferKinInfoVector fRemove​(Vector termsToRemove)
        Remove kin terms from this kin term map. Creates a kin term map that does not contain the kin terms in termsToRemove. If these terms are not in the kin term map then it is unchanged. References to these terms are also removed from generator productions, as well as all productions associated with a generator included in the list.
        Parameters:
        termsToRemove - List of kin terms to be removed from this.
        Returns:
        The current kin map. This is a convenience so that the filters can be applied inline.

      • fUnion

        public TransferKinInfoVector fUnion​(TransferKinInfoVector union)
        Finds the union of this kin term map with another Creates a kin term map that contains all kin terms in this and the kin term map union. Note that the union only includes the set of productions currently in the two kin term maps. Use fMerge to restore cross references between the terms in the two maps that might have been lost in earlier transformations.
        Only this kin term map will be altered. The parameter kin term map will never be changed.
        Parameters:
        union - The kin term map to be added to this.
        Returns:
        The current kin map. This is a convenience so that the filters can be applied inline.

      • fDifference

        public TransferKinInfoVector fDifference​(TransferKinInfoVector diff)
        Finds the difference of this kin term map with another Creates a kin term map that contains only kin terms in this that are not shared with the kin term map diff. This includes the difference of generator productions - only productions that are different are retained.
        Only this kin term map will be altered. The parameter kin term map will never be changed.
        Parameters:
        diff - The kin term map to be removed from this.
        Returns:
        The current kin map. This is a convenience so that the filters can be applied inline.

      • fIntersection

        public TransferKinInfoVector fIntersection​(TransferKinInfoVector intersect)
        Finds the intersection of this kin term map with another Creates a kin term map that contains all kin terms in this that are shared with intersect. This includes the intersection of generator productions - only productions that are in common are reported.
        Only this kin term map will be altered. The parameter kin term map will never be changed.
        Parameters:
        intersect - The kin term map to be intersected with this.
        Returns:
        The current kin map. This is a convenience so that the filters can be applied inline.

      • fMerge

        public TransferKinInfoVector fMerge​(TransferKinInfoVector merge,
                                    TransferKinInfoVector unity)
        Merges this kin term map with another This merges by examining the original kin term map that both maps were derived from, and re-inserts generator productions for each map that include references to terms in the other map. The object is to produce a complete kin term map with respect to the included relationships. The results should be identical to a map that was created by removing terms that are in neither of the present kin term maps. Only this kin term map will be altered. The parameter map will never be changed.
        Parameters:
        merge - The kin term map to be merged into this.
        unity - The original kin term map from which both this and merge were derived.
        Returns:
        The current kin map. This is a convenience so that the filters can be applied inline.
